Source: ztlp
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Steven Price <steve@techrockstars.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 13), erlang-dev (>= 1:24), elixir (>= 1.12), cargo
Standards-Version: 4.6.0
Homepage: https://ztlp.org
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/priceflex/ztlp.git

Package: ztlp-relay
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser, erlang-base (>= 1:24)
Description: ZTLP Relay - Zero Trust Layer Protocol relay node
 The ZTLP relay forwards encrypted traffic between nodes in a Zero
 Trust Layer Protocol network. Supports standalone and mesh
 configurations with consistent-hash routing, PathScore-based relay
 selection, and multi-hop forwarding.

Package: ztlp-gateway
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser, erlang-base (>= 1:24)
Description: ZTLP Gateway - Zero Trust Layer Protocol TCP bridge
 The ZTLP gateway bridges ZTLP sessions to TCP backend services.
 Performs full Noise_XX handshake as responder, policy-based access
 control, identity resolution via ZTLP-NS, and audit logging.

Package: ztlp-ns
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, adduser, erlang-base (>= 1:24)
Description: ZTLP-NS - Zero Trust Layer Protocol namespace server
 Distributed namespace server for ZTLP identity resolution.
 Ed25519-signed records, hierarchical zone delegation, revocation,
 Mnesia-backed persistent storage, and bootstrap discovery.

Package: ztlp-cli
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: ZTLP CLI - Zero Trust Layer Protocol command-line tool
 Unified CLI for ZTLP operations: key generation, peer connections,
 packet inspection, relay management, namespace queries, and
 diagnostic tools (ping, inspect, load generator, fuzzer).

Package: ztlp
Architecture: all
Depends: ztlp-relay, ztlp-gateway, ztlp-ns, ztlp-cli
Description: ZTLP - Zero Trust Layer Protocol (meta-package)
 Installs all ZTLP components: relay, gateway, namespace server,
 and CLI tool. Identity-first network overlay on existing IP
 infrastructure.
